const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Do you serve all of Monte Sano including the mountain roads?",
    answer: "Yes! We serve the entire Monte Sano area including homes along Monte Sano Boulevard, Bankhead Parkway, Panorama Drive, and the winding mountain roads throughout the community. Our teams are comfortable navigating the mountain terrain and accessing homes at various elevations. Whether you're near the state park entrance or tucked away on a private lane, we'll find you."
  },
  {
    question: "How do you handle mountain homes with multiple levels built into hillsides?",
    answer: "Monte Sano homes often feature unique multi-level designs that follow the mountain topography - walkout basements, split levels, and rooms at various elevations. We're experienced cleaning these architectural layouts efficiently. Our teams bring adequate staff for larger properties and understand how to navigate homes where stairs connect different living areas throughout."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you clean our large windows with mountain views?",
    answer: "Absolutely! Those stunning valley and mountain views are one of Monte Sano's best features, and they deserve spotless windows. Interior window cleaning is included in our deep cleaning service. We carefully clean your windows and tracks so you can enjoy unobstructed views of the city lights, sunset panoramas, and natural surroundings."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you have experience with older established Monte Sano homes?",
    answer: "Yes, many Monte Sano homes date back decades, featuring solid construction, original hardwood, stone fireplaces, and craftsmanship you simply don't find in newer builds. We respect and properly care for these vintage elements while also handling any modern updates. Original wood floors, natural stone surfaces, and classic fixtures all receive appropriate treatment."
  },
  {
    question: "How do you handle homes surrounded by nature - dust, pollen, leaves?",
    answer: "Living among the trees means nature finds its way inside. We understand Monte Sano's unique challenges - pollen in spring, leaves tracking in during fall, and the general dust that comes with forest living. Our regular maintenance addresses these ongoing issues, and deep cleaning tackles the seasonal buildup that accumulates in mountain homes."
  },
  {
    question: "Can you work around our schedule if we work from home?",
    answer: "Many Monte Sano residents work from home, enjoying the peaceful mountain setting. We can absolutely work around your schedule and home office needs. Clean during your lunch break, focus on certain areas while you're in meetings, or schedule us when you're away. We're flexible and understand the work-from-home lifestyle."
  },
  {
    question: "What about vacation homes or seasonal residents?",
    answer: "Monte Sano has both year-round residents and those who use their mountain property seasonally or as a retreat. We offer services for both - regular maintenance for full-time residents and pre-arrival/post-departure cleaning for those who come and go. We can coordinate with property managers and provide condition reports if needed."
  },
  {
    question: "Do you clean outdoor living spaces like screened porches and decks?",
    answer: "While we primarily focus on interior cleaning, we can clean screened porches, sunrooms, and covered outdoor living areas that are essentially extensions of your home. Many Monte Sano properties feature these transitional spaces designed to enjoy the mountain setting. Let us know what outdoor areas you'd like included in your service."
  }
];

